    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 5a: \"In cultured hippocampal neurons transfected with an N-terminal GFP-tagged phactr construct, subcellular distribution was throughout cell bodies and dendrites, with apparent enrichment in dendritic spines. Phactr-1 was found in the perinuclear region but was absent from cell nuclei.\"\n\nFigure 5b: \"Subcellular fractionation of rat brain homogenate supported the observation that phactr-1 may be localized at synapses because the protein was found to be present in postsynaptic density (PSD) fractions.\". Experimental description: we annotate against rat species, as this is the endogenous protein observed in Figure 5: \"Subcellular fractionation of rat brain homogenate supported the observation that phactr-1 may be localized at synapses because the protein was found to be present in postsynaptic density (PSD) fractions\"",
